cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) using small feed-forward neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses techniques for obtaining small neural network models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper explores different tradeoffs when allocating a small memory budget, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for some experiments, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV).
